This paper is primarily focused on security and privacy concerns related to process accounting data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a tool that uses anonymization techniques, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the tool is designed to promote sharing of process accounting logs, which could relate to software engineering (cs.SE) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
